According to the 2020 U.S. Census, Culpeper's population stood at 20,062. &#91;52&#93; The racial composition was as follows: 49.3% White (non-Hispanic), 17.3% Black or African American, 2.4% Asian, 0.8% Native American or other races, and 5.4% identifying with two or more races. Those of Hispanic or Latino origin constituted 24.9% of the total population. &#91;53&#93;

